bug.short_desc: [type wizards] Creating class pkg1.A that implements/extends type pkg2.A result in code with error

long_desc.thetext:
Also tried with class pkg1.A extends class pkg2.A. generate the code:
class A extends A { => error }
Bug present in 3.8.1
To reproduce the bug no need for the code snippet given in the first comment, just using the File > New > Class dialog do the trick.
ImportRewrite#findInImports is not reporting resource with conflicting name. Re-assigning to core. See comment 3 on how to reproduce the issue.

Created attachment 240787 Experimental Patch
In ImportRewrite#findInImports added the condition to find resource with conflicting name. This seems to have solved the issue.
Thank you Mathew! Do you have any idea if the fix will be available on 3.9.2 via the usual update site or if it will have to wait for Luna ?

(In reply to Adrien Constancin from comment #6) > Thank you Mathew! > Do you have any idea if the fix will be available on 3.9.2 via the usual > update site or if it will have to wait for Luna ?
Currently the focus is on Java 8, hence not sure whether this issue will be taken up by the JDT/core team.
Thank you, I'll do a workaround until then (setting the new class to another name by example... if I don't change it too much people may not even notice :D )
Any love for this small bug?
Manoj, please take a look at this.

Created attachment 248600 JDT UI test failures
There are many test failures in JDT UI (see attached screenshot). Looks like the fix also needs to be corrected. For example, InferTypeArgumentsTests.testCuSuperAndSub() results in: List<p.Super> l= list; instead of (expected): List<Super> l= list;

Thanks Noopur. I've reverted the fix via commit: http://git.eclipse.org/c/jdt/eclipse.jdt.core.git/commit/?id=cea68c59c921f1ca5c01091f0bfe74894257a349
*** Bug 420579 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***

Created attachment 248619 Fix
(In reply to Jayaprakash Arthanareeswaran from comment #12) > Did you mean to add more to the catch block? Or just the TODO has to be > removed?
The fix had more coding deficits like unnecessary null checks, usage of simpleName.toString(), and iterating ICompilationUnit types after the astRoot types have already been processed. And it didn't account for the case where qualifier.equals(packageName).
The problem is a variant of the problems that were solved with bug 235253, bug 194358, and bug 295638. I think the added functionality should only be enabled when useContextToFilterImplicitImports is set.
All JDT UI tests and ImportRewriteTest are green, and the New Class wizard is also fixed (comment 3).
